### 3. Implementation Roadmap (How)

#### Step A: Segmented RF Source & Active Cs Control Prototyping
*   **Action:** Construct a 1/2 scale RF source (~0.2×0.4m extraction area). Deploy multi-point Langmuir probes and emission spectroscopy for Cs* line intensity imaging. Implement closed-loop PID control of Cs evaporation rates to maintain surface work function φ < 1.6eV with uniformity ±0.05eV.
*   **Acceptance Criteria:** D⁻ volume density > 5×10¹⁶ m⁻³. Cs* emission spatial non-uniformity < ±10%. D⁻/e⁻ ratio > 2 (pre-acceleration).

#### Step B: Gradient Magnetic Filter & Edge Enhancement Grid Tuning
*   **Action:** Implement axially segmented magnetic filter fields (B_max inlet → B_min outlet) to counteract E×B deflection. Install concentric Edge Enhancement Rings biased +5%~10% relative to ground to boost edge electric fields. Validate against PIC simulations.
*   **Acceptance Criteria:** Local D⁻ extraction efficiency > 55%. Large-area beam profile uniformity ≤ ±7% RMS. Electron transverse deflection separation rate > 80%.

#### Step C: Full-scale MW Source Integration & Production Validation
*   **Action:** Integrate multiple driver modules into full-size extraction area (~0.4×1.0m or equivalent 1000+ apertures). Triple-stage acceleration to 500keV. Calorimetric dump measurement and slit-scanning for uniformity. Long-term thermal cycling validation.
*   **Acceptance Criteria:** Total D⁻ beam power ≥ 1MW @ 500keV. Extraction efficiency ≥ 60%. Uniformity ≤ ±5% RMS. Post-suppression e⁻/D⁻ < 0.3. Continuous operation ≥ 300s repeatable > 10 times. Zero residual grid thermal deformation post-cooldown.

